[normal]Roads 
[normal]–
[normal] 
[normal]we are responsible for the treatment of all of London’s Red Routes, a 
[normal]              
[normal]network of 580km.  Throughout winter, a fleet of 40 gritters, all of which can 
[normal]              
[normal]be fitted with ploughs, as well as 
[normal]gritting quad bikes, flat bed trucks and teams
[normal] 
[normal]              
[normal]of operatives are on standby for deployment
[normal] across the network. 
[normal]We have 
[normal]           agreed with the 
[normal]boroughs a list of core bus routes, bus garage locations and 
[normal]           bus stands to 
[normal]ensure bus services c
[normal]an be maintained.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4
[normal]              
[normal]M
[normal]ost highway authorities have gritting networks which are prioritised by use, 
[normal]with both the 
[normal]Transport for London Road Network (TLRN)
[normal] and
[normal] the Strategic Road N
[normal]etwork
[normal] (SRN)
[normal], are treated
[normal] as high priority. The frequency and type of treatm
[normal]ent is 
[normal]dependent
[normal] on prevailing and forecast weather conditions to ensure the entire network remains operable. Reports of the planned treatments are sent to stakeholders.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5
[normal]              
