[normal]Command and control
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.14
[normal]              
[normal]We 
[normal]use the ‘Gold’, ‘Silver’, ‘Bronze’ structure. This relates to the role that each person within the command structure will play as opposed to ‘rank’, the
[normal] roles being Strategic, Tactical and Operational respectively. It mirrors the structure utilised by the emergency services and is used by senior managers across 
[normal]TfL
[normal] on a regular basis for major planned events. The same command structure is also utilised by the Metropolitan Police’s Safer Transport Command and 
[normal]Traffic Operational Command Unit
[normal] whose operations centre
[normal],
[normal] Metrocomm
[normal],
[normal] is co-located 
[normal]with our 
[normal]Surface Transport
[normal] Traffic Control Centre
[normal] in Palestra
[normal].  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.15
[normal]              
[normal]We have 
[normal]agreed activation and communications processes with 
[normal]the LLACC
[normal], 
[normal]              
[normal]which is managed by London Fire Brigade Emergency Planning.
