[normal]3.6
[normal]              
[normal]For LU
[normal],
[normal] arrangements are in place for mutual aid with
[normal] 
[normal]regard
[normal] to gritting 
[normal]those 
[normal]              
[normal]vulnerable areas of streets outside stations and for tr
[normal]ain depot entry roads. 
[normal]              
[normal]This supports safe access to station and depot 
[normal]              
[normal]roadways, car parks and staff 
[normal]              
[normal]walkways outside stations.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.7
[normal]              
[normal]An audit of de-icing supplies (both materials and tools) at each station is 
[normal]              
[normal]completed annually in September and orders a
[normal]re placed for replenishments.  
[normal]              
[normal]Contracts are in place to continually replenish stocks throughout the season 
[normal]              
[normal](within 24 hours of station reporting use), with buffer stocks held at strategic 
[normal]              
[normal]locations across the network.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.8
[normal]              
[normal]On both LU and L
[normal]ondon 
[normal]R
[normal]ail
[normal] 
[normal]infrastructure, de-icing fluid is laid by specially adapted trains. This activity is triggered by temperature and precipitation levels in the forecast.  These are tested prior to the season.
[normal] 
[normal]Each 
[normal]Underground 
[normal]line’s stock is typically equivalent to around o
[normal]ne week of intensive use, with contracts in place for supply of more fluid at short notice.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.9
[normal]              
[normal]If snow is forecast, contracts are in place to obtain around 200 additional staff per shift to keep walkways clear, 
[normal]              
[normal]allowing the full time staff to concentra
[normal]te on specialist areas 
[normal](such as 
[normal]critical 
[normal]sets of points). 
[normal]The T
[normal]rain Operating Companies
[normal] have similar contracts.
